race.description: Ladbrokes Pakenham Cup Sat 13 Dec Maiden Plate
race.comment: FORCEOFONE (6) on top. He ran a good race first up at Sale in what was a strongly run affair, battling away well for third having started firmly in the market in a G3 race on debut before the spell. He's bred to get a trip so rising to 1400m second up looks perfect. RATHLIN EXPRESS (7) comes through the same race at Sale, finishing fourth on that occasion when not far behind FORCEOFONE. Tricky draw here but he can roll forward and give a sight. JUSTIBELLA (9) was disappointing at her second start staying at 1200m at Ballarat last time but had shown promise on debut and rising in trip should suit. MOONBOLT (5) just missed fresh at Warrnambool in an encouraging effort. Bit more depth here but 1400m looks ideal. BACK FOR MORE (1) could be an improver in his second campaign.
